Lemme see...

Connie: The original. Tall, curvy shewolf with white fur and hair, silver eyes, and a white trenchcoat+hat ensemble. Very professional attitude while on the clock, but excitable when off duty, occasionally lapsing into her more wolfish side when angry or particularly aroused.

RGB: A trio of AIs sharing a body. Body is divided into red, blue, and green thirds, and has very generous curves. In reality, is a fair bit taller than the average man. Each head has a different personality.

Xen: A jackal woman from out of this world. To say a lot about her character would spoil her stories (Spaced Out and Purple Veil).

Coyote: The trickster goddess. Lean and lithe, with blue fur decorated with geometric patterns. Very mischievous, with strange powers. Actually very caring beneath her pranksterish ways.

Alyssa: A fluffy cat married to a man with a strange olfactory disorder that brings him to orgasmic pleasure when he smells clean fur. Very much aware of this quirk and absolutely obsessed with bringing her husband to his knees in public.

Dolly: A sheep scientist who somehow operates two identical bodies that share their senses. It's... complicated.

Capra: A goat goddess of love and pleasure. Takes the guise of a mortal priestess to bring blessings to her followers. Old-fashioned, but with a sensual streak.

Lena Lynx: An old-time cartoon starlet who stepped off the screen and into reality. Very, very sentimental and nostalgic.

All the above share a loose canon; the following do not.

Pyr3: A modded SCP-1471 who can modify herself. Very flirty and mischievous.

Percy: a fungus/cat hybrid. Spent 10 years alone in an abandoned lab, and is a bit broken for it. Cannot speak intelligibly and so talks via whiteboard.

Scraggler: Literally nightmarish hound-beast who can manifest in multiple places. Needs love badly.

???: unnamed, haunted plush woman inspired by an image of a female anthro Tails Doll. Eerie and very assertive.
